<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Group Dead Trigger
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        The Event Point fires when all NPCs of a specific Colour and Group combination are dead. Used by 44 Event Points across retail missions for elimination objectives and group wipe detection.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Group Dead Trigger Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> tracks all NPCs that share a specific Colour+Group identifier and fires when
        every single one is dead. NPCs in Urban Chaos are tagged with a Colour (0-14) and Group letter (A-Z).
        This trigger monitors all NPCs with the matching Colour+Group combination and fires when none are
        alive. This is the standard way to create "eliminate all enemies" objectives.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Unlike <Bold>Killed</Bold> which tracks one specific NPC death, or <Bold>Counter</Bold> which tracks
        a partial quota, <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> requires complete elimination of an entire group. This is
        essential for "clear the area," "eliminate all hostiles," or "wipe out the gang" style objectives.
        It automatically tracks group membership — no manual counting required.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Practical meaning:</Run>
                <Run> Use Group Dead when this Event Point should fire after all NPCs of a specific Colour+Group are eliminated. Set EP Ref to the Colour (0-14) and EP Ref Bool to the Group (0=A, 1=B, etc.).</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        When To Use Group Dead Trigger
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Use <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> trigger when the Event Point should fire after all members of a Colour+Group
        are eliminated. This is appropriate for:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,8">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Total elimination objectives</Bold> - "Eliminate all enemies in the area"</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Wave completion</Bold> - Detect when an enemy wave is completely wiped out</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Area clearance</Bold> - "Clear the building of all hostiles"</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Gang wipe objectives</Bold> - "Eliminate all gang members"</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Progressive spawns</Bold> - Next wave spawns when previous wave is dead</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Clean sweep win conditions</Bold> - Mission succeeds when all enemies are dead</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Fields
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">EP Ref (Colour)</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        The Colour index (0-14) of the NPCs to track. All NPCs in the mission are tagged with a Colour for
        identification. This field specifies which Colour to monitor. When combined with EP Ref Bool (Group),
        this defines the exact Colour+Group to watch.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,4,0,0">
        <Bold>Common Colour values:</Bold>
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="40,2,0,8">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>0 = Red (typically enemies)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>1 = Blue (typically allies)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>2 = Green</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>3 = Yellow</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>...and so on up to 14</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">EP Ref Bool (Group)</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        The Group letter (0=A, 1=B, 2=C, etc.) of the NPCs to track. All NPCs are also tagged with a Group
        letter (A-Z) for sub-categorization. This field specifies which Group to monitor. When combined with
        EP Ref (Colour), this defines the exact Colour+Group to watch.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,4,0,0">
        <Bold>Group values:</Bold>
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="40,2,0,8">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>0 = Group A</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>1 = Group B</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>2 = Group C</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>...and so on (A-Z)</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,4,0,0">
        <Bold>Important:</Bold> The Colour+Group combination must match NPCs that actually exist in the
        mission. If you set EP Ref = 0 (Red) and EP Ref Bool = 0 (Group A), but no Red/Group A NPCs are
        spawned, the trigger fires immediately because zero NPCs are alive (technically all are dead).
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Behavior
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Every game frame, the trigger checks how many NPCs with the matching Colour+Group are alive. When
        the count reaches zero (all are dead), the trigger condition is met. Whether the Event Point fires
        immediately or continues to check depends on the listening mode:
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="24,2,0,8">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Active</Bold> - Fires once when all group members are dead, stays active (most common pattern)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Active While</Bold> - Active only while all group members are dead (deactivates if more spawn)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Active Time</Bold> - Fires when all are dead, stays active for After Timer duration</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Active Die</Bold> - Fires once when all are dead, immediately becomes dead</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        <Bold>Example:</Bold> A Message Event Point with <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> trigger (EP Ref = 0 [Red],
        EP Ref Bool = 0 [Group A]) and <Bold>Active</Bold> listening mode:
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="40,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Mission starts, multiple Group Life Event Points spawn Red/Group A enemies</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>This Event Point waits for all Red/Group A NPCs to die</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Player engages enemies, killing them one by one</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Trigger continues waiting while at least one Red/Group A enemy is alive</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Player kills the last Red/Group A enemy</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>All Red/Group A NPCs are now dead (count = 0)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Trigger condition is met, Event Point fires</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Message "All hostiles eliminated" appears</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Event Point becomes active and stays active (using Active listening mode)</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Common Patterns
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Total Elimination Win Condition
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Multiple Group Life Event Points spawn Red/Group A enemies throughout the mission. A Group Dead
        trigger (EP Ref = 0 [Red], EP Ref Bool = 0 [Group A], Active) fires a Win Event Point when all
        enemies are dead. This is the most common use of Group Dead in retail missions — "kill all enemies
        to win."
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Wave Completion Detection
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Event Point A spawns wave 1 enemies as Red/Group A (Active). Event Point B is a Group Dead trigger
        (EP Ref = 0 [Red], EP Ref Bool = 0 [Group A], Active). Event Point C spawns wave 2 enemies as
        Red/Group B with Dependency on B (Active). When wave 1 is eliminated, wave 2 spawns. This creates
        progressive wave combat.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Area Clearance Objective
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Different buildings have enemies with different Colour+Group tags: Building 1 has Red/Group A,
        Building 2 has Red/Group B. Separate Group Dead triggers track each building. A Boolean And combines
        both Group Dead triggers to create "clear all buildings" objective requiring total elimination.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Gang Elimination Mission
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        A specific gang is tagged as Yellow/Group C. A Group Dead trigger (EP Ref = 3 [Yellow], EP Ref Bool = 2
        [Group C], Active) fires a Message "Gang eliminated" and unlocks the next objective. This creates
        "eliminate specific gang" missions distinct from general enemy elimination.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Progressive Difficulty
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Event Point A spawns easy enemies as Red/Group A (Active). Event Point B is a Group Dead trigger
        (EP Ref = 0 [Red], EP Ref Bool = 0 [Group A], Active). Event Point C spawns harder enemies as
        Red/Group B with Dependency on B (Active). Difficulty increases as each group is eliminated.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Retail Examples
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> trigger appears in 44 Event Points across retail missions. It's commonly used
        for total elimination win conditions and wave progression. Retail missions prefer Group Dead over
        Counter triggers for "kill all enemies" objectives because it automatically tracks group membership
        without manual counting.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Retail pattern:</Run>
                <Run> Retail missions commonly use Red/Group A for primary enemies and Group Dead → Win condition. Different Groups (B, C, D) are used for separate waves or gangs. Colours beyond Red (Blue, Green, Yellow) are used for faction-specific elimination objectives.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Important Warnings
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2" CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Colour+Group must match spawns:</Run>
                <Run> The Colour+Group values (EP Ref and EP Ref Bool) must match NPCs that actually spawn in the mission. If you set the trigger to watch Red/Group A but all enemies are Red/Group B, the trigger fires immediately because zero Red/Group A NPCs exist.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2" CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">All must die:</Run>
                <Run> Group Dead requires 100% elimination. If even one NPC of the Colour+Group is alive, the trigger won't fire. For partial quotas ("kill 10 of 15 enemies"), use Counter triggers instead. Group Dead is all-or-nothing.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2" CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Spawning more resets condition:</Run>
                <Run> If all Group members die and then more are spawned (same Colour+Group), the Group Dead condition becomes false again. The trigger will fire again when the new spawns are all dead (if using Active While), or won't fire again (if using Active).</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Comparison With Other Trigger Types
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Group Dead vs Killed</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> fires when all members of a Colour+Group are dead. <Bold>Killed</Bold> fires
        when one specific NPC dies. Use <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> for "eliminate all enemies" objectives. Use
        <Bold>Killed</Bold> for "eliminate specific target" objectives.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Group Dead vs Counter</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> requires 100% elimination of a group. <Bold>Counter</Bold> fires at a specific
        numeric threshold (can be partial). Use <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> for total wipe objectives. Use
        <Bold>Counter</Bold> for partial quotas ("kill 10 of 15 enemies").
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Group Dead vs Dependency</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> tracks NPC deaths. <Bold>Dependency</Bold> waits for Event Points to fire.
        Use <Bold>Group Dead</Bold> for elimination tracking. Use <Bold>Dependency</Bold> for event sequencing.
        Often combined: Group Dead fires, next Event Point has Dependency on it.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Basic Group Dead Trigger Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Identify which enemies should be eliminated (one wave, one gang, all enemies, etc.)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Choose a unique Colour+Group combination for those enemies (e.g., Red/Group A)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create or configure Group Life Event Points that spawn those enemies</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set each Group Life's Colour to the chosen Colour (e.g., 0 for Red)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set each Group Life's Group to the chosen Group (e.g., 0 for Group A)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create the Event Point that should fire when all enemies are dead</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set Trigger to <Bold>Group Dead</Bold></Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set EP Ref to the Colour value (0-14, matching the enemy Colour)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set EP Ref Bool to the Group value (0=A, 1=B, etc., matching the enemy Group)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set Listening Mode (usually Active for elimination objectives)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Test in-game by killing all but one enemy</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Verify the trigger does NOT fire (one enemy still alive)</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Kill the last enemy</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Verify the trigger fires immediately when the last enemy dies</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Verify the Colour+Group combination matches the spawned enemies</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Authoring tip:</Run>
                <Run> Use consistent Colour+Group conventions across your missions: Red/Group A for primary enemies, Red/Group B for wave 2, Blue/Group A for allies, etc. Document your Colour+Group assignments in comments. This makes Group Dead triggers much easier to configure and debug.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>
